020package com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.api;
021
022import com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.grammar.javadoc.JavadocCommentsLexer;
023
024/**
025 * Contains the constants for all the tokens contained in the Abstract
026 * Syntax Tree for the javadoc grammar.
027 *
028 * @see <a href="https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/tools/unix/javadoc.html">
029 *     javadoc - The Java API Documentation Generator</a>
030 */
031public final class JavadocCommentsTokenTypes {
032
033    /**
034     * Root node of any Javadoc comment.
035     *
036     * <p><b>Tree for example:</b></p>
037     * <pre>{@code
038     * JAVADOC_CONTENT -> JAVADOC_CONTENT
039     * |--LEADING_ASTERISK -> *
040     * |--NEWLINE -> \n
041     * |--LEADING_ASTERISK -> *
042     * |--NEWLINE -> \n
043     * |--LEADING_ASTERISK -> *
044     * `--NEWLINE -> \n
045     * }</pre>
046     */
047    public static final int JAVADOC_CONTENT = JavadocCommentsLexer.JAVADOC;
048
049    /**
050     * Leading asterisk used to format Javadoc lines.
051     */
052    public static final int LEADING_ASTERISK = JavadocCommentsLexer.LEADING_ASTERISK;
053
054    /**
055     * Newline character in a Javadoc comment.
056     */
057    public static final int NEWLINE = JavadocCommentsLexer.NEWLINE;
058
059    /**
060     * Plain text content within a Javadoc comment.
061     */
062    public static final int TEXT = JavadocCommentsLexer.TEXT;
063
064    // Block tags
065
066    /**
067     * General block tag (e.g. {@code @param}, {@code @return}).
068     */
069    public static final int JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG;
070
071    /**
072     * At-sign {@code @} that starts a block tag.
073     */
074    public static final int AT_SIGN = JavadocCommentsLexer.AT_SIGN;
075
076    /**
077     * {@code @author} Javadoc block tag.
078     *
079     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have one child:</p>
080     * <ol>
081     *  <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION}</li>
082     * </ol>
083     *
084     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
085     * <pre>{@code * @author name.}</pre>
086     * <b>Tree:</b>
087     * <pre>{@code
088     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
089     * `--AUTHOR_BLOCK_TAG -> AUTHOR_BLOCK_TAG
090     *    |--AT_SIGN -> @
091     *    |--TAG_NAME -> author
092     *    `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
093     *        `--TEXT ->  name.
094     * }</pre>
095     *
096     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
097     */
098    public static final int AUTHOR_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.AUTHOR_BLOCK_TAG;
099
100    /**
101     * {@code @deprecated} block tag.
102     */
103    public static final int DEPRECATED_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.DEPRECATED_BLOCK_TAG;
104
105    /**
106     * {@code @param} Javadoc block tag.
107     *
108     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have two children:</p>
109     * <ol>
110     *  <li>{@link #PARAMETER_NAME}</li>
111     *  <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION}</li>
112     * </ol>
113     *
114     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
115     * <pre>{@code * @param value The parameter of method.}</pre>
116     * <b>Tree:</b>
117     * <pre>{@code
118     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
119     * `--PARAM_BLOCK_TAG -> PARAM_BLOCK_TAG
120     *    |--AT_SIGN -> @
121     *    |--TAG_NAME -> param
122     *    |--TEXT ->
123     *    |--PARAMETER_NAME -> value
124     *    `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
125     *        `--TEXT ->  The parameter of method.
126     * }</pre>
127     *
128     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
129     */
130    public static final int PARAM_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.PARAM_BLOCK_TAG;
131
132    /**
133     * {@code @return} Javadoc block tag.
134     *
135     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have one child:</p>
136     * <ol>
137     *  <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION}</li>
138     * </ol>
139     *
140     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
141     * <pre>{@code * @return The return of method.}</pre>
142     * <b>Tree:</b>
143     * <pre>{@code
144     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
145     * `--RETURN_BLOCK_TAG -> RETURN_BLOCK_TAG
146     *    |--AT_SIGN -> @
147     *    |--TAG_NAME -> return
148     *    `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
149     *        `--TEXT ->  The return of method.
150     * }</pre>
151     *
152     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
153     */
154    public static final int RETURN_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.RETURN_BLOCK_TAG;
155
156    /**
157     * {@code @throws} Javadoc block tag.
158     *
159     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have two children:</p>
160     * <ol>
161     *  <li>{@link #IDENTIFIER} - the exception class</li>
162     *  <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION} - description</li>
163     * </ol>
164     *
165     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
166     * <pre>{@code * @throws IOException if an I/O error occurs}</pre>
167     * <b>Tree:</b>
168     * <pre>{@code
169     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
170     * `--THROWS_BLOCK_TAG -> THROWS_BLOCK_TAG
171     *     |--AT_SIGN -> @
172     *     |--TAG_NAME -> throws
173     *     |--TEXT ->
174     *     |--IDENTIFIER -> IOException
175     *     `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
176     *         `--TEXT ->  if an I/O error occurs
177     * }</pre>
178     *
179     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
180     */
181    public static final int THROWS_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.THROWS_BLOCK_TAG;
182
183    /**
184     * {@code @exception} Javadoc block tag.
185     *
186     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have two children:</p>
187     * <ol>
188     *  <li>{@link #IDENTIFIER}</li>
189     *  <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION}</li>
190     * </ol>
191     *
192     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
193     * <pre>{@code * @exception FileNotFoundException when file is not found.}</pre>
194     * <b>Tree:</b>
195     * <pre>{@code
196     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
197     * `--EXCEPTION_BLOCK_TAG -> EXCEPTION_BLOCK_TAG
198     *    |--AT_SIGN -> @
199     *    |--TAG_NAME -> exception
200     *    |--TEXT ->
201     *    |--IDENTIFIER -> FileNotFoundException
202     *    `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
203     *        `--TEXT -> when file is not found.
204     * }</pre>
205     *
206     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
207     */
208    public static final int EXCEPTION_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.EXCEPTION_BLOCK_TAG;
209
210    /**
211     * {@code @since} Javadoc block tag.
212     *
213     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have one child:</p>
214     * <ol>
215     *   <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION}</li>
216     * </ol>
217     *
218     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
219     * <pre>{@code * @since 1.0}</pre>
220     *
221     * <b>Tree:</b>
222     * <pre>{@code
223     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
224     * `--SINCE_BLOCK_TAG -> SINCE_BLOCK_TAG
225     *    |--AT_SIGN -> @
226     *    |--TAG_NAME -> since
227     *    `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
228     *        `--TEXT ->  1.0
229     * }</pre>
230     *
231     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
232     */
233    public static final int SINCE_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.SINCE_BLOCK_TAG;
234
235    /**
236     * {@code @version} Javadoc block tag.
237     *
238     * <p>This tag has only one argument — {@link #TEXT}:</p>
239     *
240     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
241     * <pre>{@code * @version value}</pre>
242     * <b>Tree:</b>
243     * <pre>{@code
244     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
245     * `--VERSION_BLOCK_TAG -> VERSION_BLOCK_TAG
246     *    |--AT_SIGN -> @
247     *    |--TAG_NAME -> version
248     *    `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
249     *        `--TEXT ->  value
250     * }</pre>
251     *
252     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
253     */
254    public static final int VERSION_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.VERSION_BLOCK_TAG;
255
256    /**
257     * {@code @see} block tag.
258     */
259    public static final int SEE_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.SEE_BLOCK_TAG;
260
261    /**
262     * {@code @hidden} Javadoc block tag.
263     *
264     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have one child:</p>
265     * <ol>
266     *   <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION} – optional description text</li>
267     * </ol>
268     *
269     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
270     * <pre>{@code * @hidden value}</pre>
271     *
272     * <b>Tree:</b>
273     * <pre>{@code
274     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
275     * `--HIDDEN_BLOCK_TAG -> HIDDEN_BLOCK_TAG
276     *     |--AT_SIGN -> @
277     *     |--TAG_NAME -> hidden
278     *     `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
279     *         `--TEXT ->  value
280     * }</pre>
281     *
282     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
283     */
284    public static final int HIDDEN_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.HIDDEN_BLOCK_TAG;
285
286    /**
287     * {@code @uses} Javadoc block tag.
288     *
289     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have one child:</p>
290     * <ol>
291     *   <li>{@link #IDENTIFIER} – the referenced service type</li>
292     * </ol>
293     *
294     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
295     * <pre>{@code * @uses com.example.app.MyService}</pre>
296     *
297     * <b>Tree:</b>
298     * <pre>{@code
299     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
300     * `--USES_BLOCK_TAG -> USES_BLOCK_TAG
301     *    |--AT_SIGN -> @
302     *    |--TAG_NAME -> uses
303     *    |--TEXT ->
304     *    `--IDENTIFIER -> com.example.app.MyService
305     * }</pre>
306     *
307     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
308     */
309    public static final int USES_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.USES_BLOCK_TAG;
310
311    /**
312     * {@code @provides} block tag.
313     *
314     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have two children:</p>
315     * <ol>
316     *  <li>{@link #IDENTIFIER}</li>
317     *  <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION}</li>
318     * </ol>
319     *
320     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
321     * <pre>{@code * @provides com.example.MyService with com.example.MyServiceImpl}</pre>
322     *
323     * <b>Tree:</b>
324     * <pre>{@code
325     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
326     * `--PROVIDES_BLOCK_TAG -> PROVIDES_BLOCK_TAG
327     *    |--AT_SIGN -> @
328     *    |--TAG_NAME -> provides
329     *    |--TEXT ->
330     *    |--IDENTIFIER -> com.example.MyService
331     *    `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
332     *        `--TEXT ->  with com.example.MyServiceImpl
333     * }</pre>
334     *
335     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
336     */
337    public static final int PROVIDES_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.PROVIDES_BLOCK_TAG;
338
339    /**
340     * {@code @serial} block tag.
341     *
342     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have one child:</p>
343     * <ol>
344     *   <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION} – optional description text</li>
345     * </ol>
346     *
347     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
348     * <pre>{@code * @serial include}</pre>
349     *
350     * <b>Tree:</b>
351     * <pre>{@code
352     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
353     * `--SERIAL_BLOCK_TAG -> SERIAL_BLOCK_TAG
354     *   |--AT_SIGN -> @
355     *   |--TAG_NAME -> serial
356     *   `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
357     *       `--TEXT ->  include
358     * }</pre>
359     *
360     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
361     */
362    public static final int SERIAL_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.SERIAL_BLOCK_TAG;
363
364    /**
365     * {@code @serialData} block tag.
366     *
367     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have one child:</p>
368     * <ol>
369     *   <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION} – optional description text</li>
370     * </ol>
371     *
372     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
373     * <pre>{@code * @serialData data description value}</pre>
374     *
375     * <b>Tree:</b>
376     * <pre>{@code
377     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
378     * `--SERIAL_DATA_BLOCK_TAG -> SERIAL_DATA_BLOCK_TAG
379     *    |--AT_SIGN -> @
380     *    |--TAG_NAME -> serialData
381     *    `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
382     *        `--TEXT ->  data description value
383     * }</pre>
384     *
385     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
386     */
387    public static final int SERIAL_DATA_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.SERIAL_DATA_BLOCK_TAG;
388
389    /**
390     * {@code @serialField} Javadoc block tag.
391     *
392     * <p>Such Javadoc tag can have three children:</p>
393     * <ol>
394     *   <li>{@link #IDENTIFIER} – field name</li>
395     *   <li>{@link #FIELD_TYPE} – field type</li>
396     *   <li>{@link #DESCRIPTION} – field description</li>
397     * </ol>
398     *
399     * <p><b>Example:</b></p>
400     * <pre>{@code * @serialField name String The person's full name.}</pre>
401     *
402     * <b>Tree:</b>
403     * <pre>{@code
404     * JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG -> JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
405     * `--SERIAL_FIELD_BLOCK_TAG -> SERIAL_FIELD_BLOCK_TAG
406     *     |--AT_SIGN -> @
407     *     |--TAG_NAME -> serialField
408     *     |--TEXT ->
409     *     |--IDENTIFIER -> name
410     *     |--TEXT ->
411     *     |--FIELD_TYPE -> String
412     *     `--DESCRIPTION -> DESCRIPTION
413     *         `--TEXT ->  The person's full name.
414     * }</pre>
415     *
416     * @see #JAVADOC_BLOCK_TAG
417     */
418    public static final int SERIAL_FIELD_BLOCK_TAG = JavadocCommentsLexer.SERIAL_FIELD_BLOCK_TAG;
419
